BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9OPGe-hXAh8Uv3s6-52F9
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260327T072418Z
DTSTART:20260402T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-04
	-02T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-04-02T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:XZ4NHZPw8vmGKPD8TFiRO
SUMMARY:Scott Gibson - Visual Symphony II
DTSTAMP:20260327T072418Z
DTSTART:20260402T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:In March\, Visual Symphony II Scott Gibson invites viewers into
	 a world where music and art collide. Each work is an exploration of the v
	ivid\, sensory experience of sound translating into vibrant\, emotional vi
	suals. As an artist with synesthesia each work expresses Scott’s personal 
	perception of what music looks like. Scott uses resin techniques that he h
	as pioneered and pushes the boundaries of this medium.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symphony-ii/18280602/202
	6-04-02T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symph
	ony-ii/18280602/2026-04-02T00
LOCATION:Gray Sky Gallery\, 320 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
